</%args>
<%init>
</%init>

	<& "menu.mas", 
		tourn          => $tourn,
		tourn_settings => $tourn_settings,
		person         => $person,
		whoami         => "reset"
	&>

	<div class="main">


		<div class="centeralign full">
			<h4 class="redtext">DELETE DATA FROM <% $tourn->name %></h4>
		</div>

			<p> 
				What you are about to do is delete the following records from
				the database <b>permanently</b>.  No, you cannot get them back.
				No, it doesn't matter if you didn't mean it.  They will simply
				be gone, baby, gone.  Don't come crying to me after the
				fact.
			</p>

			<h4>Delete all panels & rounds:</h4>
			
			<form action="reset_panels.mas" method="post">

			<div class="row full">

				<span class="half rightalign redtext strong">
					Type "I am certain" to continue:
				</span>

				<span class="threeeighths">
					<input 
						type           = "text"
						name           = "certain"
						size           = "32"
						autocomplete   = "off"
						autocorrect    = "off"
						autocapitalize = "off"
						spellcheck     = "false"
						class          = "martop notfirst"
					>
				</span>

				<span class="eighth">
					<input  type="submit" value="Delete">
					</form>
				</span>

			</div>

			<h4>Delete all timeslots, panels & rounds:</h4>
			
